### Question 10: Scaling Yourself Out
*"SelfPM was built for you. How do you make it work for users who aren't you? What assumptions are baked in that wouldn't apply to others?"*

The main assumption that I’ve made that applies to me, and maybe not to others, is that, I really fucking want to do this. The level of instrinic motivation is quite high for me, because this is coming following very many years of failure. So, if other seekers are not there yet, then, that may hurt how some of these features work / succeed, compared to how I perceive them to. 



